revision.text:
{{Refimprove|date=August 2015}} The '''Arabic Toilers' Movement''' ({{lang-ar|حركة الكادحين العرب}}) was a [[political party]] in [[Iraq]]. It was founded in 1962, by a group that broke away from the [[Arab Socialist Baath Party]] who had adopted a [[Marxism-Leninism|Marxist-Leninist]] political line. After November 18, 1964, the Arabic Toilers' Movement began seeking cooperation with other Iraqi political forces as well as Dr. [[George Habash]]. The organization began cooperating with the [[Arab Socialist Union (Iraq)|Arab Socialist Union]] in the same year.<ref name="hizb">ʻUlaywī, Hādī Ḥasan. ''al-Aḥzāb al-siyāsīyah fī al-ʻIrāq: al-sirrīyah wa-al-ʻalanīyah''. [[Beirut]]: Riyāḍ al-Rayyis lil-Kutub wa-al-Nashr, 2001. p. 189.</ref>
The organization did not last long, as several of its founders left and joined other political parties.<ref name="hizb"/>
