{{Infobox person | name = Maurice Rollet | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date|df=yes|1933|1|30}} | birth_place = [[Joigny]], [[France]] | death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|2014|1|21|1933|1|30}} | death_place = | nationality = French | education = | home_town = | occupation = Poet, activist and medical doctor | years_active = | spouse = }}
'''Maurice Rollet''' (30 January 1933–21 January 2014) was a French poet, activist and medical doctor. He sometimes used the pseudonym ''François Le Cap''.
== Biography == In the 1960s he was a far right-wing activist who was involved with ''[[Jeune Nation]]'', ''[[Europe-Action]]'' and supported the [[Organisation armée secrète|OAS]], for which he was imprisoned. In 1968 he was one of the co-founders of the ''[[Nouvelle Droite]]'' organization [[GRECE]]. According to Rollet the organization was founded at his birthday party in [[Marseille]] on 29 January 1968, although this account has been contested.<ref>Jean-Yves Camus, Nicolas Lebourg. 2017. ''Far-Right Politics in Europe''. p. 133. {{ISBN|9780674971530}}</ref>
In 1973 he co-founded the [[Modern Paganism|neopagan]] scouting organization [[Europe Jeunesse]] with [[Jean-Claude Valla]] and [[Jean Mabire]].<ref>Camus and Lebourg 2017. p. 142.</ref> Unlike some ''Nouvelle Droite'' activists who mainly regarded paganism as an intellectual position, Rollet always took the pagan sensibility very seriously. He held contact with the [[European Congress of Ethnic Religions|World Congress of Ethnic Religions]] based in [[Vilnius]].<ref>Stéphane François. 2009. [https://core.ac.uk/download/pdf/47805466.pdf Les paganismes de la Nouvelle Droite (1980-2004)]. p. 467-68.</ref>
His poetic works are marked by his neopaganism. Some of his lyrics have been set to music by the singer [[Docteur Merlin]].<ref>[https://fr.novopress.info/153474/deces-maurice-rollet/ Décès de Maurice Rollet].</ref>
He appeared as a film actor in ''[[The Rebel (1980 French film)|The Rebel]]'' in 1980<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cinema.encyclopedie.films.bifi.fr/imprime.php?pk=46809|title=Le Rebelle - CF|website=cinema.encyclopedie.films.bifi.fr}}</ref> and ''[[La Flambeuse]]'' in 1981<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cinema.encyclopedie.films.bifi.fr/imprime.php?pk=51772|title=La Flambeuse - CF|website=cinema.encyclopedie.films.bifi.fr}}</ref> and composed music for ''[[Pierre and Djemila]]'' in 1986.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cinema.encyclopedie.films.bifi.fr/imprime.php?pk=46918|title=Pierre et Djemila - CF|website=cinema.encyclopedie.films.bifi.fr}}</ref>
