{{Politics of Paraguay}}
A '''referendum on [[absentee ballot|allowing expatriate citizens to vote]]''' was held in [[Paraguay]] on 9 October 2011.<ref>[http://www.paraguaymipais.com.ar/comunidad-paraguaya/2011/05/el-9-de-octubre-se-hara-referendum-por-voto-paraguayo-en-el-exterior/ El 9 de octubre se hará referéndum por voto paraguayo en el Exterior] Paraguay Mi País, 8 May 2011 {{es icon}}</ref> The measure was approved by 78% of voters, although [[voter turnout]] was only 12.5%. If approved by the [[Congress of Paraguay|Congress]], the measure would give the right to vote to more than half a million Paraguayans living abroad, mostly in [[Argentina]], [[Spain]] and the [[United States]]. President [[Fernando Lugo]] believed it would strengthen Paraguay's democracy.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-15234483 Paraguay referendum backs voting rights for expatriates] BBC News, 10 October 2011</ref>
